# Erie.pro persona separation

## Principle

**One page → one primary audience → one primary job.**

Do not mix consumer CTAs with provider sales on the same page.

| Audience | Primary job | Zone |
|----------|-------------|------|
| **consumer** | Find, trust, contact providers | `/`, `/directory`, `/get-matched`, `/[niche]`, `/[niche]/[provider]`, `/areas/*` |
| **provider** | Claim, subscribe, manage microsite & billing | `/pros`, `/for-business/*`, `/dashboard/*`, `/providers/*`, `/provider/*` |
| **admin** | Operations only | `/admin/*` |

## CTA policy (`allowProviderCTA`)

- **consumer pages:** `footer-utility` only — e.g. “Own this business?” text link at page footer. No hero banners, no sidebar claim cards, no provider growth scorecards.
- **provider pages:** provider CTAs may be primary.
- **admin pages:** no marketing CTAs.

## Forbidden on consumer surfaces

- “Claim this territory/category” as primary CTA
- Provider growth scorecard / “Become a pro” hero blocks
- Exclusive-provider / territory sales copy in hero or main column

## Implementation

- Registry: `src/lib/page-audience-registry.ts`
- Helpers: `src/lib/audience-context.ts`
- Runtime nav: `src/components/audience/audience-provider.tsx` + `site-header-nav.tsx`
- AI copy locks: `src/lib/audience-content-prompts.ts`
- Architecture doc: `docs/ERIE_PRO_PERSONA_ARCHITECTURE.md`

